    <h1 class="text-6xl font-semibold tracking-[-2.5px]">What is Generative Engine Optimization?</h1>
  </div>

  <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none text-lg">
    <p class="lead">Generative Engine Optimization (GEO) is the practice of optimizing content so that it is more likely to be cited, referenced, and surfaced by AI-powered generative search engines.</p>

    <h2>The New Gatekeepers</h2>
    <p>Millions of people now receive answers directly from large language models instead of clicking through traditional search results. These models synthesize information from across the web and present it as a single, authoritative response.</p>

    <p>In this environment, being ranked #1 on Google is no longer enough. You must become one of the few sources that the model chooses to trust and cite.</p>

    <h2>Key Characteristics of GEO</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Authority over ranking</strong> — Models prioritize trustworthy, expert sources</li>
      <li><strong>Originality matters</strong> — Unique insights and data outperform generic content</li>
      <li><strong>Structure enables citation</strong> — Clear, scannable content is easier for models to extract</li>
      <li><strong>E-E-A-T is amplified</strong> — Experience, Expertise, Authoritativeness, and Trustworthiness are critical</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>